"euaCostEUR":null,"euaPriceUSD":null,"euaPriceEUR":null,"euaVerified":null,"euaEstimated":null,"euaPurchased":null,"euaBalance":null}},{"portName":"Garyville LA (using Reserve)","displayOrder":1,"co2":413.852400000000000000,"eeoi":10.754321742143580000,"aer":6.050594696104448000,"soxMt":0.739200000000000000,"sox":0.019208767743747610,"noxMt":13.079999999999998000,"nox":0.339895403257871600,"euEtsDetails":{"allowancePurchases":null,"eua":0.000000000000000000,"euaCostUSD":null,"euaCostEUR":null,"euaPriceUSD":null,"euaPriceEUR":null,"euaVerified":null,"euaEstimated":null,"euaPurchased":null,"euaBalance":null}}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-15T17:04:26.967","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"fda in Tampico and Veracruz less than pda"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-05-07T17:30:54.063","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"Kalk Bay delivered to Stena Bulk at Savannah after vessel\u0027s maiden voyage carrying Palms with tank cleaning for our account. For peace of mind we employed Lighthouse Marine Services for remote cleaning support. LMS did not agree with the cleaning chemicals already on the vessel so suggested we purchase a suite of Marclean chems through them due time constraint and availability. Inclusive of delivery costs this ran us about $30k. Vessel ended up delayed at Savannah for an additional 2.5 weeks and ultimately did not use any chemicals when preparing for Gasoline due good practice steaming COTs as they completed.\n\n \n\nBunkers and on hire survey planned for arrival Miss River but charterers wanted to load as soon as possible so agreed to cover tug turn cost after loading. However, during overnight inbound maneuvers Marathon terminal did not answer calls from agent which forced us to anchor and await signs of life. Meanwhile the bunker barge was waiting so we capitalized on free time and berthed after the stem. \n\n \n\nExecuted voyage added 2 disports in Mexico, each adding $63k to total freight. Overall vessel sat on demurrage for 16.5 days at $56,400/day adding to PnL. March bunker hedge settled with a positive $14,746 and March FFAs settled at $23,528."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-29T13:08:27.627","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Vsl was delayed sailing due to issue with customs and crew change. To be discussed if rebilled to owners."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-17T19:49:23.683","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"4 days added to Tampico estimate/demurrage"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-17T15:55:28.73","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"two addiitional disports added in Mex, updated with additional freight/port costs/demurrage estimates"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-16T13:04:32.243","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"2 berthings at Progreso, demurrgae estimate added plus LS for shifting"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-10T19:31:28.533","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"port costs basis PDA at Progreso 17k more than generated"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-08T14:17:57.057","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"demurrage estimate added basis ETS Progreso"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-08T10:08:38.983","modifiedByFull":"Andersen, Thomas","remark":"Updated settlement of bunker hedges \u002B FFAS for March-24  \u002B38,274 USD / TCE \u002B2,921 USD"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-05T13:39:27.883","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"time extended to include waiting samples green light at outer anchorage"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-04T19:41:14.373","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"BOD price updated, slight increase/mt"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-03T12:33:07.347","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"arrival date moved back 24h due drifting awaiting laycan // disport changed to Progreso reducing laden passage // demurrage estimate added"}],"offhireList":[{"id":198233,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":280962,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantit